description: A utility to help generate a file containing information about dependencies including the full license text.
sites_https_justification: Website, repository, and download URLs are all on https://github.com
contribution_justification: Non-trivial contribution file in repository: <https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md>.
contribution_requirements_justification: https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md The contributing page details standards for submitting Pull Requests as well as expectations for commit messages, but no publishes coding standards exist today. However, this package does use a utility called StyleCI which automatically evaluates changes against community-driven PHP standards (PSR-2, among others) and opens a pull request with style fixes (see https://styleci.io/ for more information).
license_location_justification: Non-trivial license location file in repository: <https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/LICENSE>.
floss_license_justification: The Apache-2.0 license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
floss_license_osi_justification: The Apache-2.0 license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
documentation_basics_justification: Installation, Usage, and Output examples present in the README <https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/README.md>
documentation_interface_justification: The README provides details on how to run the utility with various flags (input) and provides an example of the generated output. https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/README.md
repo_public_justification: Repository on GitHub, which provides public git repositories with URLs.
repo_track_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git can track the changes, who made them, and when they were made.
repo_interim_justification: Internal work (from maintainers) is done in branches and pulled into master with a pull request. External work is merged via pull requests. Both paths have opportunity for review before being released.
repo_distributed_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git is distributed.
version_unique_justification: As a PHP package primarily consumed by the PHP dependency manager Composer (getcomposer.org), this package follows the versioning standards specified on Packagist (the repository for Composer packages): https://packagist.org/about#managing-package-versions. Composer (the utility) is to packagist.org, as npm (the utility) is to npmjs.org.
version_tags_justification: This PHP package follows the recommendations of packagist.org, and publishes changes using git tags and GitHub releases.
release_notes_justification: Release objects are created from tags on Github, with descriptive titles, extra descriptions when required, and credit to the author(s). https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/releases
release_notes_vulns_justification: As of yet, no CVE vulnerabilities have been identified.
report_tracker_justification: Using the Issues feature on github.com, Issues can be assigned to a contributor, tagged with labels, assigned to a project or milestone, etc. They can also link to other Issues or Pull Requests.
report_responses_justification: At the time of answering this question, this project has had only one bug report that was acknowledged (and fixed) on the same day: https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/issues/1
report_archive_justification: Github maintains a list of all open and closed issues for public perusal: https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/issues
vulnerability_report_process_justificati: Reporting process detailed in the readme: https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/README.md
vulnerability_report_private_justificati: Process for reporting sensitive information included in readme: https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/README.md
vulnerability_report_response_justificat: No vulnerability reports received to date.
build_justification: This utility is downloaded and "installed" through a dependency manager, Composer. It functions similarly to NPM packages.
test_justification: Uses phpunit unit tests and are run automatically in GitLab CI/CD.
test_invocation_justification: phpunit is the standard unit test suite for PHP applications.
test_policy_justification: A line in the CONTRIBUTING.md file indicated that new unit tests should be added or existing tests be modified, as applicable, for any new code changes.
tests_are_added_justification: Policy on tests is new, and no major functionality has yet been added.
tests_documented_added_justification: Policy is documented in the CONTRIBUTING.md file, which is to be followed for every content change.
warnings_justification: StyleCI analyzes the code upon every push and will automatically submit a PR with style/syntax changes to fit the configuration I set.
crypto_published_justification: No cryptographic functionality in this package.
crypto_call_justification: This utility does not implement cryptography.
crypto_floss_justification: This utility does not depend on cryptography (except for referencing git commit hash strings, but those are generated by git itself, and not part of this package).
crypto_keylength_justification: This utility does not implement or depend on cryptography.
crypto_working_justification: This utility does not implement or depend on cryptography (the hashes referenced by the package are generated by git directly, and only used as any other string).

vulnerabilities_critical_fixed_justifica: No known vulnerabilities have yet been discovered/announced.
static_analysis_justification: This project uses Gitlab CI, and uses some of their built-in security testing. For SAST, it uses both phpcs-security-audit and a plugin called "secrets" (that checks for passwords in the code repo).
static_analysis_common_vulnerabilities_j: Using Gitlab CI, we have enabled a number of different SAST tools, most of which check for PHP-specific vulnerabilities or anti-patterns.
static_analysis_fixed_justification: No vulnerabilities identified as of yet.
static_analysis_often_justification: Gitlab CI is configured to run the various analyzers for every commit on every branch.
dynamic_analysis_justification: This project does not include any web accessible inputs (is not a web app at all) and does not directly consume user input, other than a command name to process. The "input" is a composer.lock file, a json file generated by the PHP dependency manager Composer. Additional validation on the generated lock file will be implemented in the future.
dynamic_analysis_unsafe_justification: Project not implemented using a memory-unsafe language.
dynamic_analysis_enable_assertions_justi: This project does not include any web accessible inputs (is not a web app at all) and does not directly consume user input, other than a command name to process. crypto_weaknesses_justification: This utility does not implement or depend on cryptography.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: Unit tests, dependency scanning, and SAST is run every push to the code base, and upon every merge.
discussion_justification: GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests, which are both enabled for this project.
no_leaked_credentials_justification: No credentials are involved with this utility.
english_justification: All documentation is written in English, and primary maintainer reads/writes/speaks English for bug reports / feature requests.
crypto_used_network_justification: This project does not perform any network communication.
crypto_tls12_justification: This project does not perform any network communication.
crypto_certificate_verification_justific: This project does not perform any network communication.
crypto_verification_private_justificatio: This project does not perform any network communication.

build_reproducible_justification: No building occurs for this project.
dco_justification: Comcast OSS projects use an app called CLAassistant. You can see all contributors to the project have signed the CLA. And example is here: https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/pull/4
access_continuity_justification: Admins of the Comcast org on GitHub have owner rights on all repositories within it. https://github.com/orgs/Comcast/people?utf8=%E2%9C%93&query=+role%3Aowner
documentation_quick_start_justification: Fast installation with Composer dependency manager and the basic usage of the utility is documented in the readme: https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/README.md
documentation_current_justification: When applicable, the README is updated along with and functional change submitted via pull request.
documentation_achievements_justification: Badge would be displayed on the readme, which is shown on the project homepage on GitHub, along with existing badges: https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses
accessibility_best_practices_justificati: Utility is entirely command-line driven, and ANSI-colors are only used to highlight certain information, but does not indicate any critical content.
internationalization_justification: Other than the textual commands required to interact with the utility, all output generated comes from other code repositories (dependencies).
sites_password_security_justification: Project site is simply the github repository page.
maintenance_or_update_justification: Update instructions are listed in the README: https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/README.md
vulnerability_report_credit_justificatio: No vulnerabilities reported nor resolved in the last 12 months. When they do occur, reporters will be credited in the CONTRIBUTORS file, if they so desire. https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/CONTRIBUTORS.md
vulnerability_response_process_justifica: Security Vulnerability Reporting instructions are listed in the README: https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/README.md
coding_standards_justification: This package uses a third-party utility called StyleCi (https://styleci.io/) that automatically reviews incoming pull requests, applies configurable coding standards, and issues a pull request of its own with code style changes.
coding_standards_enforced_justification: See answer for [coding_standards] above, as well as https://styleci.io/.
build_standard_variables_justification: No builds are required for this utility.
build_preserve_debug_justification: No builds are required for this utility.
build_non_recursive_justification: No builds are required for this utility.
build_repeatable_justification: No builds are required for this utility.
installation_standard_variables_justific: This package is installed through the use of PHP's Dependency Manager, Composer. Regardless if the package is installed globally or as an application dependency, it is installed in either the default composer location, or wherever the user tells composer to install dependencies.
installation_development_quick_justifica: All required PHP extensions and packages to support development and testing are explicitly listed in the composer.json file: https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/composer.json
external_dependencies_justification: External dependencies are both explicitly and implicitly listed in the projects composer.json (https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/composer.json). Explicitly listed dependencies are those directly required by this package. Implicitly listed dependencies are those the required dependencies depend on themselves.
dependency_monitoring_justification: Dependency checks are done with gemnasium, a Gitlab product, during Gitlab CI pipelines: https://github.com/Comcast/php-legal-licenses/blob/master/.gitlab-ci.yml
updateable_reused_components_justificati: Using the Composer dependency manager for PHP, all third-party source code is kept separate from application code, and is easy to update.
input_validation_justification: The only inputs to the utility are command line arguments, that must meet a set of expected options. If the argument(s) do not match expectations, and error is thrown and the utility exits.
crypto_algorithm_agility_justification: This project does not use cryptography in any form.
crypto_credential_agility_justification: This project does not use authentication/keys of any kind.
